          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-2041 osd: inconsistent OI cache",
        "message": "LU-2041 osd: inconsistent OI cache\n\nosd_it_ea_rec() can put inconsistent information in OI cache\nif osd_ea_fid_get() failed, then we might get wrong ino and load\nwrong inode in later call. This may cause data corruption or\nother unpredictable failure.\n\nThis patch also fixed a bug in osd_iget_verify().\n\nSigned-off-by: Wang Di <di.wang@whamcloud.com>\nSigned-off-by: Liang Zhen <liang@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I219f74d40250f74d5111c236728ce02d549fb7e4\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b2_3"
    }
